class AverageMeter(object):
    # Source: https://github.com/filipradenovic/
    """Computes and stores the average and current value"""

    def __init__(self):
        self.reset()

    def reset(self):
        """Reset all the metrics"""
        self.val = 0
        self.avg = 0
        self.sum = 0
        self.count = 0

    def update(self, val, n=1):
        """Update the metrics"""
        self.val = val
        self.sum += val * n
        self.count += n
        self.avg = self.sum / self.count

def count_labels(data_loader):
    """Counts the number of occurrences of each label in a data loader.

    Parameters
    ----------
    data_loader : torch.utils.data.DataLoader
        DataLoader instance that provides batches of data in the form (data, labels).

    Returns
    -------
    label_counts : defaultdict(int)
        Default dict with labels as keys and counts as values.
    """
    label_counts = defaultdict(int)

    for _, labels in data_loader:
        for label in labels:
            label_counts[label.item()] += 1

    return label_counts

def print_dataloader_information(dataloader, dataset_name):
    label_counts = count_labels(dataloader).items()
    label_counts = sorted(label_counts, key=lambda x: x[0])

    print(
        f"{dataset_name}\n" f"\tSize: {len(dataloader.dataset):,}\n",
        f"\t\tNumber of batches: {len(dataloader):,}\n",
        f"\t\tBatch size: {dataloader.batch_size:,}\n",
        f"\tClass Counts:",
    )

    for label, count in label_counts:
        print(f"\t\t{label}: {count:,}")

def print_matrix(matrix, indent):
    if isinstance(matrix, torch.Tensor):
        matrix = matrix.numpy()

    for i in range(matrix.shape[0]):
        print(indent, end="")
        for j in range(matrix.shape[1]):
            print(f"{matrix[i, j]:.3f}", end=HTAB)
        print()

def print_avg_t(matrix_list):
    stacked_matrices = torch.stack(matrix_list)

    mean_matrix = torch.mean(stacked_matrices, dim=0)
    std_matrix = torch.std(stacked_matrices, dim=0)

    for i in range(mean_matrix.size(0)):
        for j in range(mean_matrix.size(1)):
            print(HTAB + f"{mean_matrix[i, j]:.3f} ± {std_matrix[i, j]:.3f}", end=HTAB)
        print()

def display_random_dataset_images(
    dataset_name, transform=None, num_images=9, title=None, seed=42
):
    """Display random images in a single plot.

    Parameters
    ----------
    dataset : DatasetClass
        An instance of DatasetClass.
    transform : bool, optional
        Whether to apply image transformations to the dataset, by default None
    num_images : int, optional
        Number of random images to display, by default 9
    title : str, optional
        Title of the plot, by default None
    seed : int, optional
        Random seed, by default 42
    """
    # check dataset name
    assert dataset_name in DATASET_NAMES, "Invalid dataset name"

    # create dataset from name
    dataset = create_dataset_class(dataset_name, transform=transform)

    # Set random seed
    np.random.seed(seed)

    # Randomly select indices
    random_indices = np.random.choice(len(dataset), num_images)

    # Create a 3x3 grid to display images
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 3, figsize=(6, 6))

    for i, ax in enumerate(axes.flat):
        idx = random_indices[i]
        image, label = dataset[idx]

        # If the image is a tensor, convert it back to a numpy array
        if isinstance(image, torch.Tensor):
            image = image.permute(1, 2, 0).numpy()

        # Rescale the pixel values to [0, 1] if they are not in this range
        if image.min() < 0 or image.max() > 1:
            image = (image - image.min()) / (image.max() - image.min())

        # Display the image and label
        ax.imshow(image)
        ax.set_title(f"Label: {label}")
        ax.axis("off")

    if title:
        fig.suptitle(title)

    plt.show()

def plot_images_from_batch(data_loader, loader_name, batch_num, num_images=16):
    """Plots a specified number of images from a specified batch of a data loader.

    Parameters
    ----------
    data_loader : torch.utils.data.DataLoader
        Data loader containing the dataset
    loader_name : str
        The name of the data loader
    batch_num : int
        The batch number to plot from
    num_images : int
        The number of images to plot, default 16
    """
    for i, (images, labels) in enumerate(data_loader):
        if i == batch_num:
            # Calculate number of rows and columns for the grid
            num_rows = math.ceil(math.sqrt(num_images))
            num_cols = math.ceil(num_images / num_rows)

            fig, axes = plt.subplots(num_rows, num_cols, figsize=(6, 6))
            plt.suptitle(
                f"First {num_images} Images from {loader_name} Batch {i}", fontsize=12
            )

            for j, ax in enumerate(axes.flat):
                if j >= num_images:
                    ax.axis("off")  # Turn off axes for empty subplots
                    continue

                image = images[j].numpy().transpose((1, 2, 0))

                # Rescale the pixel values to [0, 1] if they are not in this range
                if image.min() < 0 or image.max() > 1:
                    image = (image - image.min()) / (image.max() - image.min())

                ax.imshow(image)
                ax.set_title(f"Label: {labels[j].item()}")
                ax.axis("off")

            plt.show()
            break

def plot_results(train_acc, val_acc, train_loss, val_loss, name=None):
    """Plots training and validation accuracy and loss for a given dataset and model.

    Parameters
    ----------
    train_acc : list
        Training accuracy over epochs
    val_acc : list
        Validation accuracy over epochs
    train_loss : list
        Training loss over epochs
    val_loss : list
        Validation accuracy over epochs
    name : str, optional
        "Dataset_Model_T-method" information, used to annotate the plot and name the saved file, by default None
    """
    plot_specs = {
        "Dataset": name.split("_")[0],
        "Model": name.split("_")[1],
        "T-Method": name.split("_")[2],
    }

    plot_strings = []
    max_len = max([(len(k) + len(v)) for k, v in plot_specs.items()])

    # format strings
    for k, v in plot_specs.items():
        len_diff = max_len - (len(k) + len(v))

        if len(k + v) < max_len:
            len_diff += max_len - (len(k) + len(v)) - 1
        adjusted_string = f"{k}: " + v.rjust(len_diff + len(v))
        plot_strings.append(adjusted_string)

    txt_string = "\n".join(plot_strings)

    # set theme
    sns.set_theme()

    f, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, sharex=True)

    # set figure size
    f.set_figwidth(12)
    f.set_figheight(5)

    # Accuracy plots.
    ax1.plot(train_acc, color="lightsteelblue", linestyle="-", label="Train Accuracy")
    ax1.plot(val_acc, color="darkorchid", linestyle="-", label="Validation Accuracy")
    ax1.set_xlabel("Epoch")
    ax1.set_ylabel("Accuracy")
    ax1.legend()

    # Loss plots.
    ax2.plot(train_loss, color="sandybrown", linestyle="-", label="Train Loss")
    ax2.plot(val_loss, color="orangered", linestyle="-", label="Validation Loss")
    ax2.set_xlabel("Epoch")
    ax2.set_ylabel("Loss")
    ax2.legend()

    props = dict(
        boxstyle="round", facecolor="cornflowerblue", alpha=0.2, pad=0.5, linewidth=0.2
    )

    # add text box
    ax2.text(
        2.2,
        0.915,
        txt_string,
        transform=ax1.transAxes,
        fontsize=8,
        bbox=props,
    )

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(os.path.join(OUT_DIR_FIGS, name + "_acc_loss.png"))
    plt.show()

Early Stopper¶

In [449]:
class EarlyStopper:
    """Utility class for early stopping during model training.

    Attributes
    ----------
    patience : int
        Number of epochs to wait before stopping
    min_delta : float
        Minimum change in validation loss to be considered an improvement
    counter : int
        Number of epochs since last improvement
    min_validation_loss : float
        Minimum validation loss achieved so far

    Methods
    -------
    early_stop(validation_loss)
        Checks if the model should stop training.

    Parameters
    ----------
    patience : int
        Number of epochs to wait before stopping, default 1
    min_delta : float
        Minimum change in validation loss to be considered an improvement, default 0
    """

    def __init__(self, patience=1, min_delta=0):
        self.patience = patience
        self.min_delta = min_delta
        self.counter = 0
        self.min_validation_loss = float("inf")

    def early_stop(self, validation_loss):
        """Checks if the model should stop training."""
        if validation_loss < self.min_validation_loss:
            self.min_validation_loss = validation_loss
            self.counter = 0
        elif validation_loss > (self.min_validation_loss + self.min_delta):
            self.counter += 1
            if self.counter >= self.patience:
                return True
        return False

class DatasetClass(Dataset):
    """Custom dataset class for image and label data compatible with PyTorch.

    Attributes
    ----------
    images : np.ndarray
        Array of images (n, w, h, c)
    labels : np.ndarray
        Array of labels (n, )
    transform : torchvision.transforms.transforms.Compose, optional
        Compose object combining several transformations, by default None
    n_classes : int
        Number of classes
    image_width : int
        Image width
    image_height : int
        Image height
    is_RGB : bool
        Whether the image is RGB

    Methods
    -------
    __init__(self, images, labels, transform=None)
        Initialise dataset class.
    __len__(self)
        Returns the total number of images in the dataset.
    __getitem__(self, idx)
        Retrieves the image and label at the given index, applying transformations if specified.

    Parameters
    ----------
    images : np.ndarry
        Array of images, expected to be of shape (n, w, h, c).
    labels : np.ndarray
        Array of labels, expected to be of shape (n, ).
    transformations : torchvision.transforms.transforms.Compose, optional
        Compose object combining several transformations, by default None

    """

    def __init__(self, images, labels, transform=None):
        self.images = images
        self.labels = labels
        self.transform = transform

        self.n_classes = len(np.unique(labels))

        self.image_width = images.shape[1]
        self.image_height = images.shape[2]
        try:
            self.is_RGB = images.shape[3] == 3
        except IndexError:
            self.is_RGB = False

    def __len__(self):
        return len(self.images)

    def __getitem__(self, idx):
        if torch.is_tensor(idx):
            idx = idx.tolist()

        image = self.images[idx]
        label = self.labels[idx]

        if self.transform:
            image = self.transform(image)

        return image, label

def create_dataset_class(dataset_name, train=True, transform=None):
    """Creates an instance of DatasetClass for the specified dataset.

    Parameters
    ----------
    dataset_name : str
        The name of the dataset to load. Must be on fo the predefined dataset names.
    train : bool, optional
        Flag indicating whether to load the training dataset (True) or the testing dataset (False), by default True
    transform : torchvision.transforms.transforms.compose, optional
        Compose object containing list of image transformations to apply, by default None

    Returns
    -------
    DatasetClass
        An instance of the DatasetClass containing the loaded images and labels.

    Raises
    ------
    ValueError
        If the dataset_name is not in the list of predefined dataset names.
    """
    # check if dataset_name is valid
    if dataset_name not in DATASET_NAMES:
        raise ValueError(
            f"dataset_name must be one of {DATASET_NAMES}, but got {dataset_name}"
        )

    # Load the dataset
    df = np.load(DATA_PATHS[dataset_name])

    # Select appropriate data split
    images, labels = (df["Xtr"], df["Str"]) if train else (df["Xts"], df["Yts"])

    # Create and return dataset instance
    return DatasetClass(images, labels, transform=transform)

def get_dataset_loaders(
    dataset_name, transform, batch_size=32, num_workers=0, verbose=0, seed=0
):
    """Creates data loaders for the specified dataset using provided transformations.

    Parameters
    ----------
    dataset_name : str
        Name of the dataset (CIFAR, MNIST5, MNIST6)
    transformations : torchvision.transforms.transforms.Compose
        Compose object combining several transformations
    batch_size : int
        Number of samples per batch to load (default is 32).
    num_workers : int
        The number of subprocesses to use for data loading (default is 0).
    verbose : int
        Verbosity mode (0 = silent, >0 = print information) (default is 0).
    seed : int
        Random seed for shuffling and transformations (default is 0).

    Returns
    -------
    data_specs : dict
        A dictionary containing the dataset specifications.
    train_loader : torch.utils.data.DataLoader
        Data loader for the training set
    val_loader : torch.utils.data.DataLoader
        Data loader for the validation set
    test_loader : torch.utils.data.DataLoader
        Data loader for the test set

    Notes
    -----
    The train/validation split is hardcoded to 80/20 percent. Adjust the lengths in the
    random_split function call to change this ratio.
    """
    # Set the random seed for reproducibility
    torch.manual_seed(seed)

    # Create DatasetClass objects
    train_dataset = create_dataset_class(dataset_name, train=True, transform=transform)
    test_dataset = create_dataset_class(dataset_name, train=False, transform=transform)

    # Access and retain some info about the dataset
    data_specs = {
        "n_classes": train_dataset.n_classes,
        "image_width": train_dataset.image_width,
        "image_height": train_dataset.image_height,
        "is_RGB": train_dataset.is_RGB,
    }

    # Splitting training dataset into training and validation
    train_dataset, val_dataset = random_split(
        dataset=train_dataset,
        lengths=[
            0.8,
            0.2,
        ],  # Got floating point arithmetic errors when trying to parametrise this.
        generator=torch.Generator().manual_seed(seed),
    )

    # Creating data loaders
    train_loader = DataLoader(
        dataset=train_dataset,
        batch_size=batch_size,
        num_workers=num_workers,
        shuffle=True,
    )
    val_loader = DataLoader(
        dataset=val_dataset,
        batch_size=batch_size,
        num_workers=num_workers,
        shuffle=False,
    )
    test_loader = DataLoader(
        dataset=test_dataset,
        batch_size=batch_size,
        num_workers=num_workers,
        shuffle=False,
    )

    if verbose:
        print_dataset_information(
            dataset_name, data_specs, train_loader, val_loader, test_loader
        )

    return data_specs, train_loader, val_loader, test_loader

def preliminary_loss(output, labels):
    """Computes the cross-entropy loss and the predicted labels.

    Parameters
    ----------
    output : torch.Tensor
        The raw output (logits) from a model. The shape should be (batch_size, num_classes).
    labels : torch.Tensor
        The true labels for the output data. The shape should be (batch_size,).

    Returns
    -------
    loss : torch.Tensor
        The computed cross-entropy loss.
    preds : torch.Tensor
        The predicted labels for the output data.
    """
    # Initialise the loss criterion
    criterion = torch.nn.CrossEntropyLoss()

    # Calculate probabilities using softmax
    probabilities = output.softmax(dim=1)

    # Calculate loss using criterion
    loss = criterion(output, labels)

    # Get predictions from the probabilities
    _, preds = torch.max(probabilities.data, 1)

    return loss, preds

def backward_correction(predictions, targets, T):
    """Calculates loss and applies backward correction.

    Parameters
    ----------
    predictions : torch.Tensor
        The logits output from the model, expected to be of shape (batch_size, num_classes).
    targets : torch.Tensor
        The true labels for the output data, expected to be of shape (batch_size,).
    T : torch.Tensor
        The transition matrix used for backward correction, expected to be of shape (num_classes, num_classes).


    Returns
    -------
    loss : torch.Tensor
        The mean cross-entropy loss after applying backward correction.
    corrected_preds : torch.Tensor
        The predicted class labels after correction, obtained by taking the argmax of the corrected probabilities.

    """
    eps = 1e-7  # for numerical stability
    T_inv = torch.inverse(T).to(device)

    # convert targets to one-hot
    targets = torch.eye(predictions.shape[1])[targets.cpu()].to(device)

    # convert preds from logits to prob
    y_pred = torch.clamp(predictions.softmax(-1), eps, 1 - eps)

    # adjust targets with T
    targets = torch.inner(targets, T_inv)

    # calculate cross entropy loss for each batch
    losses = -torch.sum(targets * torch.log(y_pred), dim=-1)
    loss = losses.mean()

    return loss, y_pred.argmax(dim=1)

def forward_correction(predictions, target, T):
    """Calculates the corrected cross-entropy loss using forward correction with a transition matrix.

    Parameters
    ----------
    predictions : torch.Tensor
        The logits output from the model, expected to be of shape (batch_size, num_classes).
    target : torch.Tensor
        The true labels for the output data, expected to be of shape (batch_size,).
    T : torch.Tensor
        The transition matrix used for forward correction, expected to be of shape (num_classes, num_classes).

    Returns
    -------
    loss : torch.Tensor
        The mean cross-entropy loss after applying forward correction.
    corrected_preds : torch.Tensor
        The predicted class labels after correction, obtained by taking the argmax of the corrected probabilities.

    """
    eps = 1e-7
    T = T.to(device)

    # convert targets to one-hot
    target = torch.eye(predictions.shape[1])[target.cpu()].to(device)

    # Convert preds from logits to prob
    y_pred = torch.clamp(predictions.softmax(-1), eps, 1 - eps)

    # Adust probs with T
    y_pred = torch.inner(y_pred, T)

    # Calculate cross entropy loss for each batch
    losses = -torch.sum(target * torch.log(y_pred), dim=-1)
    loss = losses.mean()

    return loss, y_pred.argmax(dim=1)

def importance_reweighting(predictions, target, T):
    """Calculates the loss reweighted cross-entropy loss using a transition matrix.

    Parameters
    ----------
    predictions : torch.Tensor
        The logits output from the model, expected to be of shape (batch_size, num_classes).
    target : torch.Tensor
        The true labels for the output data, expected to be of shape (batch_size,).
    T : torch.Tensor
        The transition matrix used for importance reweighting, expected to be of shape (num_classes, num_classes).

    Returns
    -------
    loss : torch.Tensor
        The mean cross-entropy loss after applying importance reweighting.
    reweighted_preds : torch.Tensor
        The predicted class labels after reweighting, obtained by taking the argmax of the reweighted probabilities.
    """
    eps = 1e-7
    T = T.to(device)

    # convert targets to one-hot
    target = torch.eye(predictions.shape[1])[target.cpu()].to(device)

    # Convert preds from logits to prob
    y_pred_raw = torch.clamp(predictions.softmax(-1), eps, 1 - eps)

    # Adust probs with T
    y_pred_adj = torch.inner(y_pred_raw, T)

    beta = y_pred_raw / y_pred_adj

    # Calculate cross entropy loss for each batch
    losses = -torch.sum(target * torch.log(beta), dim=-1)
    loss = losses.mean()

    return loss, beta.argmax(dim=1)

def init_weights(m):
    """Initialises weights using Xavier uniform initialisation for Conv2d and Linear layers.

    Parameters
    ----------
    m : torch.nn.Module
        A module or layer of a neural network.
    """
    if isinstance(m, (nn.Conv2d, nn.Linear)):
        nn.init.xavier_uniform_(m.weight)
        if m.bias is not None:
            nn.init.constant_(m.bias, 0)

def load_model(model_name, n_classes, is_RGB, pre_trained=False):
    """Loads a neural network model and initialises weights based on arguments.

    Parameters
    ----------
    model_name : str
        Name of the model to load
    n_classes : int
        Number of classes in the dataset
    is_RGB : bool
        Whether the dataset is RGB or grayscale
    pre_trained : bool, optional
        Whether to load the pre-trained model, by default False

    Returns
    -------
    model : torch.nn.Module
        The loaded and customised model instance.

    Raises
    ------
    ValueError
        If the "model_name" is not supported.
    """
    model_dict = {
        "ResNet18": resnet18,
        "GoogLeNet": GoogLeNet,
    }

    # Check model name is in supported models
    if model_name not in model_dict:
        raise ValueError(f"Unsupported model name: {model_name}")

    if pre_trained:
        if model_name == "ResNet18":
            loaded_model = resnet18(weights=ResNet18_Weights.IMAGENET1K_V1)
        elif model_name == "GoogLeNet":
            loaded_model = torchvision.models.get_model(
                "GoogLeNet", weights="IMAGENET1K_V1"
            )
    else:
        loaded_model = model_dict[model_name]()

    # Changes dimension of output layer to match number of classes
    loaded_model.fc = nn.Linear(loaded_model.fc.in_features, n_classes)

    # Special case for grayscale models
    if not is_RGB:
        # Change dimension of first convolutional layer to accept 1 channel
        loaded_model.conv1 = nn.Conv2d(1, 64, kernel_size=5, stride=2, padding=3)

    # Initialise weights
    if not pre_trained:
        loaded_model.apply(init_weights)

    return loaded_model

def train(
    model,
    train_loader,
    optimiser,
    device,
    t_matrix=None,
    t_matrix_method=None,
):
    """Trains model for one epoch using the specified data loader and optimiser.

    Parameters
    ----------
    model : torch.nn.Module
        The neural network model to be trained.
    train_loader : torch.utils.data.DataLoader
        The data loader containing the training data.
    optimiser : torch.optim.Optimizer
        The optimizer used for updating model weights.
    device : torch.device
        The device on which the model is trained (e.g., 'cuda' or 'cpu').
    t_matrix : torch.Tensor, optional
        The transition matrix for label noise correction, by default None.
    t_matrix_method : str, optional
        The method of transition matrix application. Supported methods are 'backward',
        'forward', and 'importance_reweighting'. If None, no transition matrix correction
        is applied, by default None.

    Returns
    -------
    float
        The average loss over the training data.
    float
        The average accuracy over the training data.

    Raises
    ------
    AssertionError
        If a transition matrix method is specified but no transition matrix is provided, or if an invalid
        transition matrix method is specified.
    """
    if t_matrix_method is not None:
        assert (
            t_matrix is not None
        ), "Transition matrix must be provided if transition matrix method is specified."

    losses = AverageMeter()
    accs = AverageMeter()

    model.train()

    for batch_idx, (images, labels) in enumerate(
        tqdm(train_loader, desc=TAB + "Training  : ")
    ):
        images, labels = images.to(device), labels.to(device)
        optimiser.zero_grad()

        # Forward pass
        outputs_logits = model(images)

        # Convert GoogLeNet outputs to logits
        if isinstance(outputs_logits, GoogLeNetOutputs):
            outputs_logits = torch.Tensor(outputs_logits.logits)

        # Calculate loss and predictions
        if t_matrix_method == "backward":
            loss, preds = backward_correction(outputs_logits, labels, t_matrix)
        elif t_matrix_method == "forward":
            loss, preds = forward_correction(outputs_logits, labels, t_matrix)
        elif t_matrix_method == "importance_reweighting":
            loss, preds = importance_reweighting(outputs_logits, labels, t_matrix)
        elif t_matrix_method == None or t_matrix == None:
            loss, preds = preliminary_loss(outputs_logits, labels)
        else:
            assert None, "Invalid t_matrix_method"

        # Calculate accuracy and update meters
        acc = accuracy_score(labels.cpu(), preds.cpu())
        losses.update(loss.item(), images.size(0))
        accs.update(acc, images.size(0))

        # Backward pass and optimise
        loss.backward()
        optimiser.step()

        # Clean up to free memory
        del images, labels, outputs_logits, preds

    return losses.avg, accs.avg

def validate(model, val_loader, device, t_matrix=None, t_matrix_method=None):
    """Validates model for one epoch. Returns average loss, accuracy, and all preds."""
    if t_matrix_method is not None:
        assert (
            t_matrix is not None
        ), "t_matrix must be provided if t_matrix_method is not None"

    losses = AverageMeter()
    accs = AverageMeter()

    model.eval()

    # Iterate through batches
    with torch.no_grad():
        for batch_idx, (images, labels) in enumerate(
            tqdm(val_loader, desc=TAB + "Validation: ")
        ):
            images, labels = images.to(device), labels.to(device)

            outputs_logits = model(images)

            if isinstance(
                outputs_logits, GoogLeNetOutputs
            ):  # if GoogLeNet extract logits
                outputs_logits = torch.Tensor(outputs_logits.logits)

            # Apply transition matrix
            if t_matrix_method == "backward":
                loss, preds = backward_correction(outputs_logits, labels, t_matrix)
            elif t_matrix_method == "forward":
                loss, preds = forward_correction(outputs_logits, labels, t_matrix)
            elif t_matrix_method == "importance_reweighting":
                loss, preds = importance_reweighting(outputs_logits, labels, t_matrix)
            elif t_matrix_method == None or t_matrix == None:
                loss, preds = preliminary_loss(outputs_logits, labels)
            else:
                assert None, "Invalid t_matrix_method"

            acc = accuracy_score(labels.cpu(), preds.cpu())
            losses.update(loss.item(), images.size(0))
            accs.update(acc, images.size(0))

            del images, labels, outputs_logits, preds

    return losses.avg, accs.avg

def predict(model, data_loader):
    """Gets predictions from model. Does not apply any transition matrix. ONLY USED for estimation of T, and test set evaluation."""
    model.eval()  # set model to evaluation mode

    y_true = []
    y_pred = []

    with torch.no_grad():
        for i, (images, labels) in enumerate(
            tqdm(data_loader, desc=TAB + "Testing   : ")
        ):
            images, labels = images.to(device), labels.to(device)

            outputs_logits = model(images)
            if isinstance(outputs_logits, GoogLeNetOutputs):
                outputs_logits = torch.Tensor(outputs_logits.logits)

            _, preds = preliminary_loss(outputs_logits, labels)

            y_true.extend(labels.cpu().numpy())
            y_pred.extend(preds.cpu().numpy())
    return np.array(y_pred), np.array(y_true)

def evaluateModel(model, test_loader):
    """Test model on test set data."""
    losses = AverageMeter()
    accs = AverageMeter()

    model.eval()

    criterion = torch.nn.CrossEntropyLoss()

    y_true = []
    y_pred = []

    with torch.no_grad():
        for batch_idx, (images, labels) in enumerate(
            tqdm(test_loader, desc=TAB + "Testing: ")
        ):
            images, labels = images.to(device), labels.to(device)

            outputs_logits = model(images)

            loss = criterion(outputs_logits, labels)

            preds = torch.argmax(outputs_logits, dim=1)

            acc = accuracy_score(labels.cpu(), preds.cpu())
            losses.update(loss.item(), images.size(0))
            accs.update(acc, images.size(0))

            y_true.extend(labels.cpu().numpy())
            y_pred.extend(preds.cpu().numpy())

    avg_loss = losses.avg

    print(f"Average Loss: {avg_loss:.4f}")
    print(f"Classification Report:\n{classification_report(y_true, y_pred)}")

    plot_confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred, name="CIFAR_ResNet18_None")

In [377]:
def estimate_t_matrix(predictions, labels, num_classes=3, smoothing=0.01):
    """
    Estimate the transitional matrix with anchor points.
    """
    matrix = np.zeros((num_classes, num_classes)) + smoothing

    for p, l in zip(predictions, labels):
        matrix[l][p] += 1

    matrix /= matrix.sum(axis=1, keepdims=True)  # normalise the matrix
    matrix = torch.tensor(matrix).float()
    return matrix

In [443]:
def create_optimiser_and_scheduler(model, optim_config):
    optimiser = optim.SGD(
        model.parameters(),
        lr=optim_config["base_lr"],
        momentum=optim_config["momentum"],
        weight_decay=optim_config["weight_decay"],
    )

    scheduler = ReduceLROnPlateau(
        optimiser,
        mode="min",
        factor=0.5,
        patience=1,
        verbose=True,
    )

    return optimiser, scheduler

def run_pipeline(
    num_runs,
    dataset_name,
    model_name,
    pre_trained,
    batch_size,
    optim_config,
    device,
    t_matrix=None,
    t_matrix_method=None,
    estimate_t_matrix_flag=False,
    show_figures=False,
    num_workers=0,
    seed=0,
):
    """Full pipeline for either estimating T or training a model with given T.

    Parameters
    ----------
    num_runs : int
        How many runs to perform.
    dataset_name : str
        The name of the dataset.
    model_name : str
        name of the model.
    pre_trained : bool
        Whether to use a pre-trained model.
    batch_size : int
        Batch size.
    optim_config : dict
        Optimiser configuration.
    device : str
        Device to run the model on.
    t_matrix : torch.tensor, optional
        Transition matrix, by default None
    t_matrix_method : str, optional
        The t-matrix application method, by default None
    estimate_t_matrix_flag : bool, optional
        Whether the pipeline should estimate_t or run the model, by default False (run model)
    show_figures : bool, optional
        Flag to show plots and confusion matrix, by default False
    num_workers : int, optional
        Number of workers for the data loader, by default 0
    seed : int, optional
        Randomness, by default 0

    Returns
    -------
    results : dict
        Dictionary containing the results of the experiment.
    """
    # Check model_name in model_dict
    if model_name not in MODEL_NAMES:
        raise ValueError(
            f"model_name must be on of {MODEL_NAMES}, but got {model_name}"
        )

    epochs = optim_config["epochs"]

    model_name_str = model_name + ("(PT)" if pre_trained else "")
    model_save_string = f"{dataset_name}_{model_name_str}_{t_matrix_method}"

    transform_name = dataset_name + ("_Pretrained" if pre_trained else "")
    transform = transformations_dict[transform_name]

    print_experiment_info(
        num_runs,
        epochs,
        dataset_name,
        model_name,
        pre_trained,
        batch_size,
        optim_config,
        device,
        t_matrix,
        t_matrix_method,
        estimate_t_matrix_flag,
    )

    ##############
    # Estimate T #
    ##############

    if estimate_t_matrix_flag:
        t_matrices = []  # [T1, T2, ...]

        for run in range(num_runs):
            #################################
            # Data and Model Initialisation #
            #################################
            data_specs, train_loader, val_loader, test_loader = get_dataset_loaders(
                dataset_name=dataset_name,
                transform=transform,
                batch_size=batch_size,
                num_workers=num_workers,
                seed=seed + run,
            )

            # Create model
            model = load_model(
                model_name=model_name,
                n_classes=data_specs["n_classes"],
                is_RGB=data_specs["is_RGB"],
                pre_trained=pre_trained,
            ).to(device)

            # Create optimiser and scheduler
            optimiser, scheduler = create_optimiser_and_scheduler(model, optim_config)

            early_stopper = EarlyStopper(
                patience=10, min_delta=0
            )  # stop if no improvement in 10 epochs

            best_model = None
            best_loss = float("inf")

            print(f"Run {run + 1} of {num_runs}")

            # Set seed for each run
            torch.manual_seed(seed + run)

            #################
            # Training Loop #
            #################
            for epoch in range(epochs):
                np.random.seed(seed + epoch)
                torch.manual_seed(seed + epoch)
                torch.mps.manual_seed(seed + epoch)

                train_epoch_loss, train_epoch_acc = train(
                    model=model,
                    train_loader=train_loader,
                    optimiser=optimiser,
                    device=device,
                )

                print(
                    TAB
                    + f"Loss (Training)  : {train_epoch_loss:.3f}, Accuracy (Training)  : {train_epoch_acc:.3f}"
                )

                if early_stopper.early_stop(train_epoch_loss):
                    print(TAB + "Early Stopping")
                    break
                elif train_epoch_loss < best_loss:
                    best_loss = train_epoch_loss
                    best_model = model

                # Update Learning Rate
                scheduler.step(train_epoch_loss)
                # debug printing for scheduler

            ######################
            # Estimate T for Run #
            ######################
            print(TAB + "-" * 10)
            preds, labels = predict(best_model, train_loader)
            print("\n")
            t_matrix = estimate_t_matrix(preds, labels)
            t_matrices.append(t_matrix)

            print(HTAB + HTAB + f"Estimation:")
            print_matrix(t_matrix, indent=TAB)
            print("=" * 50)

        #####################################
        # Calculate Average T Over All Runs #
        #####################################
        print("Transition Matrix Estimation Complete")
        print(f"Estimation (Over {num_runs} Runs):")
        print_avg_t(t_matrices)
        print("=" * 50)

        return t_matrices

    ###############################
    # T is Provided/Not Used Loop #
    ###############################
    else:
        full_train_losses, full_val_losses = (
            [],
            [],
        )  # [[run1 losses], [run2 losses], ...]]
        full_train_accs, full_val_accs = [], []
        test_accs, test_recalls, test_precisions, test_f1s = (
            [],
            [],
            [],
            [],
        )  # [run1_acc, run2_acc, ...]

        best_model = None

        for run in range(num_runs):
            print(f"Run {run + 1} of {num_runs}")

            best_run_model = None
            best_run_loss = float("inf")

            #########################################
            # Data loading and Model Initialisation #
            #########################################
            data_specs, train_loader, val_loader, test_loader = get_dataset_loaders(
                dataset_name=dataset_name,
                transform=transform,
                batch_size=batch_size,
                num_workers=num_workers,
                seed=seed + run,
            )

            # Create model
            model = load_model(
                model_name=model_name,
                n_classes=data_specs["n_classes"],
                is_RGB=data_specs["is_RGB"],
                pre_trained=pre_trained,
            ).to(device)

            # Create optimiser and scheduler
            optimiser, scheduler = create_optimiser_and_scheduler(model, optim_config)

            early_stopper = EarlyStopper(
                patience=10, min_delta=0
            )  # stop if no improvement in 10 epochs

            print(HTAB + "Training")

            # Initialise lists to store epoch metrics
            train_losses, val_losses = [], []
            train_accs, val_accs = [], []

            for epoch in range(epochs):
                print(HTAB + HTAB + f"[Epoch {epoch+1}/{epochs}]")

                # debug printing for scheduler
                # print(TAB + f"LR: {scheduler.get_last_lr()[0]:.6f}")

                # set manual seeds per epoch
                np.random.seed(seed + epoch)
                torch.manual_seed(seed + epoch)
                torch.mps.manual_seed(seed + epoch)

                #########
                # train #
                #########
                train_epoch_loss, train_epoch_acc = train(
                    model=model,
                    train_loader=train_loader,
                    optimiser=optimiser,
                    device=device,
                    t_matrix=t_matrix,
                    t_matrix_method=t_matrix_method,
                )

                ############
                # validate #
                ############
                val_epoch_loss, val_epoch_acc = validate(
                    model=model,
                    val_loader=val_loader,
                    device=device,
                    t_matrix=t_matrix,
                    t_matrix_method=t_matrix_method,
                )

                train_losses.append(train_epoch_loss)
                val_losses.append(val_epoch_loss)
                train_accs.append(train_epoch_acc)
                val_accs.append(val_epoch_acc)

                print(
                    TAB
                    + f"Loss (Training)  : {train_epoch_loss:.3f}, Accuracy (Training)  : {train_epoch_acc:.3f}"
                )
                print(
                    TAB
                    + f"Loss (Validation): {val_epoch_loss:.3f}, Accuracy (Validation): {val_epoch_acc:.3f}"
                )

                if early_stopper.early_stop(val_epoch_loss):
                    print(TAB + "Early Stopping")
                    break

                # Save the best model based on validation loss
                elif val_epoch_loss < best_run_loss:
                    best_run_loss = val_epoch_loss
                    best_run_model = model
                    torch.save(
                        best_run_model.state_dict(),
                        os.path.join(
                            OUT_DIR_MODELS,
                            f"{model_save_string}.pth",
                        ),
                    )

                # Update Learning Rate
                scheduler.step(val_epoch_loss)

            if show_figures:
                plot_results(
                    train_accs,
                    val_accs,
                    train_losses,
                    val_losses,
                    name=model_save_string,
                )

            print(HTAB + "-" * 20)

            ########
            # Test #
            ########
            print(HTAB + "Testing")
            # Predict
            predictions, targets = predict(best_run_model, test_loader)

            precision, recall, f1, _ = precision_recall_fscore_support(
                targets, predictions, average="weighted", zero_division=1
            )

            acc = accuracy_score(targets, predictions)

            full_train_losses.append(train_losses)
            full_val_losses.append(val_losses)
            full_train_accs.append(train_accs)
            full_val_accs.append(val_accs)

            test_accs.append(acc)
            test_recalls.append(recall)
            test_precisions.append(precision)
            test_f1s.append(f1)

            print("\n")
            print(HTAB + "Results (best model):")
            print(HTAB + HTAB + f"Accuracy: {acc:.3f}")
            print(HTAB + HTAB + f"Precision: {precision:.3f}")
            print(HTAB + HTAB + f"Recall: {recall:.3f}")
            print(HTAB + HTAB + f"F1: {f1:.3f}")

            if show_figures:
                print(
                    HTAB
                    + f"Classification Report:\n{classification_report(targets, predictions)}"
                )
                plot_confusion_matrix(targets, predictions, name=model_save_string)

            print("=" * 50)

        ##################################
        # Print Total Experiment Results #
        ##################################

        avg_accuracy, std_accuracy = np.mean(test_accs), np.std(test_accs)
        avg_recall, std_recall = np.mean(test_recalls), np.std(test_recalls)
        avg_precision, std_precision = np.mean(test_precisions), np.std(test_precisions)
        avg_f1, std_f1 = np.mean(test_f1s), np.std(test_f1s)

        print("EXPERIMENT COMPLETE")

        print(TAB + f"F1: {avg_f1:.3f} ± {std_f1:.3f}")
        print("=" * 50)

        return_results = {
            "full_train_losses": full_train_losses,
            "full_val_losses": full_val_losses,
            "full_train_accs": full_train_accs,
            "full_val_accs": full_val_accs,

        }
